    "The field has been driven by innovations across multiple domains, including electronic noses (e-noses), artificial olfactory systems, and wearable olfactory interfaces.",
    "These developments address challenges such as sensor noise, high-dimensional data, and nonlinear relationships between chemical structure and sensory perception.",
    "A review of recent studies (see Table 1) highlights the diversity of approaches in this space.",
    "The table presents various studies focused on AI applications in olfaction.",
    "These studies cover a range of topics, including deep learning models for odorant prediction, AI-driven wearable systems, and applications in health monitoring."
